  "body": "Am wondering if it would be possible to make this configurable\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/nomiclabs/buidler/blob/c3b10973740da1c9a44db05f82169bd0a6b1b95a/packages/buidler-core/src/internal/solidity/compiler/compiler-input.ts#L19-L22\r\n\r\nIn [solidity-coverage 497][1] someone is reporting a `Metadata too large` compiler error that can be resolved by setting the `useLiteralContent` flag to false. The metadata object has a 65kb size limit that's [checked at solc here][2]. \r\n\r\nCoverage injects a lot of text into the original source files and it seems to be coming up against this size limit.\r\n\r\nI could open a PR for this if adding the option to the solc configuration settings (like evmVersion) is the right approach. Or a PR for a better idea, just lmk.\r\n\r\n[1]: https://github.com/sc-forks/solidity-coverage/issues/497\r\n[2]: https://github.com/ethereum/solidity/blob/aff1e93caa42cdc8d3b4483073a1fa56a99a68b8/libsolidity/interface/CompilerStack.cpp#L1328-L1341",
